headlines.description: — Indiana Pacers fans welcomed back Caris LeVert with a loud ovation during pregame introductions. His newly former team even honored him with a highlight reel during the first timeout of the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeVert's strong finish helps Cavs rally past Pacers 120-113

headlines.description: — James Harden already made his first Philly highlight reel.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid's 25 points, 19 boards lift 76ers past Thunder 100-87

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray tied his career highs with 32 points and 15 assists to go with 10 rebounds for his 11th triple-double this season, Keldon Johnson scored 26 points and the San Antonio Spurs cruised to a 136-121 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray has 11th triple-double, Spurs roll past Hawks 136-121

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown sent a six-word missive the day before the start of the month that has proven to be prophetic for the Celtics.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 24, Celtics beat Denver for 7th straight win

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan delivered another big performance and got plenty of help along the way. It added up to a well-rounded win for the the balanced Bulls even though Zach LaVine struggled.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 35, Bulls pull away to beat Wolves 134-122

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 24 points and grabbed seven rebounds to lead the Utah Jazz to a 114-99 victory over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz win fifth straight at home, top Magic 114-99
